Point $G$ is the centroid of $\triangle DEF$, so $DG:GP = EG:GQ = 2:1$.  Therefore, $DG = \frac23(DP) = 12$ and $EG = \frac23(EQ) =16$, so applying the Pythagorean Theorem to $\triangle EGD$ gives us $DE = \sqrt{EG^2 + GD^2} = \boxed{20}$.

