[/asy]

problem:
A function $f$ from the integers to the integers is defined as follows:
\[f(n) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
n + 3 & \text{if $n$ is odd}, \\
n/2 & \text{if $n$ is even}.
\end{array}
\right.\]Suppose $k$ is odd and $f(f(f(k))) = 27.$  Find $k.$

solution:
We can write $f(x)$ as follows:
\[f(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
x^2 & \text{if $x > 0$}, \\
0 & \text{if $x = 0$}, \\
-x^2 & \text{if $x < 0$}.
\end{array}
\right.\]Hence, $f^{-1}(4) + f^{-1}(-100) = 2 + (-10) = \boxed{-8}.$

