Every minute, the minute hand moves $360 \div 60 = 6$ degrees. At 25 minutes past the hour, the minute hand is $25 \times 6 = 150$ degrees past the vertical 12:00 position. Every minute, the hour hand moves $360 \div 12 \div 60 = 0.5$ degrees. At 25 minutes past 12:00, the hour hand is $25 \times 0.5 = 12.5$ degrees past the vertical 12:00 position. The angle between the hands of the clock at 12:25 is $150 - 12.5 = \boxed{137.5\text{ degrees}}$.

