problem:
$ABCD$ is a square and $M$ and $N$ are the midpoints of $\overline{BC}$ and $\overline{CD},$ respectively.  Find $\sin \theta.$

[asy]
unitsize(1.5 cm);

draw((0,0)--(2,0)--(2,2)--(0,2)--cycle);
draw((0,0)--(2,1));
draw((0,0)--(1,2));
label("$A$", (0,0), SW);
label("$B$", (0,2), NW);
label("$C$", (2,2), NE);
label("$D$", (2,0), SE);
label("$M$", (1,2), N);
label("$N$", (2,1), E);
label("$\theta$", (.5,.5), SW);
[/asy]

solution:
We have that
\begin{align*}
\frac{1 - \cos \theta}{\sin \theta} - \frac{\sin \theta}{1 + \cos \theta} &= \frac{(1 - \cos \theta)(1 + \cos \theta) - \sin^2 \theta}{\sin \theta (1 + \cos \theta)} \\
&= \frac{1 - \cos^2 \theta - \sin^2 \theta}{\sin \theta (1 + \cos \theta)} \\
&= \boxed{0}.
\end{align*}

By the Law of Sines applied to triangle $OAB$, $$\frac{OB}{\sin\angle
OAB}=\frac{AB}{\sin\angle AOB}.$$With $AB = 1$ and $\angle AOB = 30^\circ$, we have \[\frac{OB}{\sin \angle OAB} = \frac{1}{\sin 30^\circ} = 2,\]so  so $OB=2\sin\angle OAB$. Thus, $OB \le \boxed{2}$, with equality if and only if $\angle OAB=90^\circ$.

[asy]
unitsize(1.5 cm);

pair O, A, B;

O = (0,0);
A = sqrt(3)*dir(30);
B = (2,0);

